// Labeled chunks for src/citations/extractor.find_candidates (regex pre-filter).
// Regex recall is the HARD CEILING of the citation graph: the README states
// chunks with no candidate span never reach the LLM classifier, so a miss here
// is permanent data loss. Recall is the primary metric; precision is secondary
// (the LLM filters false positives downstream).
//
// schema: {id, format, text, expected_keys: [canonical_key, ...]}
//   expected_keys == []  -> negative (tests false-positive rate)
//
// NOTE: seed set authored to cover known citation shapes. EXPAND with real OCR'd
// ΦΕΚ chunks — especially the line-wrap / multi-ref / FEK-prefixed variants that
// production text actually produces.
